    "For the relation extraction task, Nayak and Ng (2020) contrasted two models: text-to-text generation and copy mechanism-based decoding.",
    "However, the findings did not definitively establish the superiority of any approach.",
    "AbstR CT CDC P # component 6,089 3,279 4,931 # relation 3,832 2,060 1,220 # components with multiple parents 0 31 160 % words in nonargumentative span 2 28.09 49.30 0 Hu and Wan (2023) showed how successful T5 is in analysing sentence structures and suggested using it for sentence-level RST parsing as a type of text-to-text generation.",
    "Their work encourages us to consider argument mining, a subset of document structural analysis, as a text generation problem rather than a traditional natural language understanding one.",
    "We suggest utilising T5 within the TANL framework to tackle this text-to-text generation issue, which may be a noteworthy solution."
